From: OpenEuler Yocto <openeuler@openeuler.org>
Date: Mon, 19 May 2025 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] crypto: gracefully handle missing gpg and gpgme modules

When building dnf as a native tool in Yocto, neither python3-gpg nor
python3-gpgme (the older SWIG-based bindings) may be available in the
native sysroot. Wrapping the fallback 'import gpgme' in its own
try/except prevents a ModuleNotFoundError from propagating at import
time and allows dnf-native to run when GPG signature verification is
not actually needed (e.g., for unsigned local Yocto package feeds).

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [Yocto-specific build environment]

Signed-off-by: OpenEuler Yocto <openeuler@openeuler.org>
---
 dnf/crypto.py | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dnf/crypto.py b/dnf/crypto.py
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/dnf/crypto.py
+++ b/dnf/crypto.py
@@ -35,7 +35,10 @@
     from gpg import Context
     from gpg import Data
 except ImportError:
-    import gpgme
+    try:
+        import gpgme
+    except ImportError:
+        gpgme = None
 
 
     class Context(object):
